                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1940: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-01T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 1, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 2—2:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1571. For Alling from Hoskins. In connection my cable August 27<note n="98"
                        xml:id="d847fn98">Telegram No. 122, <ref target="#pg_806">p.
                        806</ref>.</note> from Basra Moose cabled from Jidda on August 30 that Yusuf
                    Yassin on Saturday gave Wikeley detailed account of my discussions in Jidda.
                    Moose said he assumed London probably knew results of my visit already.
                    [Hoskins.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
